6.10	Danny_Harris	Danny Harris	Danny Lee Harris (born September 7, 1965 in Torrance, California) is a former American 400m hurdles runner who won silver medals at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles and the 1987 World Championships in Rome, both behind Edwin Moses. His time of 48.02 in 1984 at age 18 is still the current World Junior Record.	
